    "title": "Mid-Level Fleet Manager at FedEx India",
    "description": "An exciting career opportunity awaits you at FedEx India. We are on the lookout for a dedicated Fleet Manager to strengthen our Dhanbad-based team.\n\nAbout FedEx India:\nFedEx India is a leading organization in the On-site sector, committed to excellence, innovation, and employee growth. We offer a dynamic work environment where talent is recognized and rewarded.\n\nKey Responsibilities:\n• Prepare MIS reports on delivery performance and SLA adherence\n• Optimize delivery routes to reduce cost and improve efficiency\n• Manage a fleet of vehicles and coordinate with drivers\n• Implement cost-saving initiatives in transportation and warehousing\n• Manage relationships with third-party logistics providers\n• Manage reverse logistics and return merchandise authorization\n• Coordinate with warehousing teams for inbound and outbound operations\n\nRequired Skills & Qualifications:\n• Bachelor's degree in a relevant field\n• 3-6 years of relevant experience\n• Proficiency in ERP Systems\n• Proficiency in Supply Chain Management\n• Proficiency in WMS\n• Proficiency in Last Mile Delivery\n• Proficiency in KPI Monitoring\n• Proficiency in Vendor Management\n• Proficiency in Reverse Logistics\n• Proficiency in MS Excel\n\nWork Mode: On-site - Work from our office\n\nWhat We Offer:\n• International travel opportunities for senior roles\n• Meal coupons and food allowance\n• Maternity and paternity leave\n• Company-sponsored certifications\n• Work-from-home flexibility\n• Referral bonus program\n• Salary Range: 7 LPA - 15 LPA per annum\n\nLocation: Dhanbad, Jharkhand, India\n\nIf you are excited about this opportunity, apply now and take the next step in your career journey with FedEx India!",
